subaward_description:
THE CONTRACTOR SHALL PROVIDE ENGINEERING SERVICES TO SUPPORT THE ENHANCEMENT, OPERATION, MAINTENANCE,
AND SUSTAINMENT OF THE SWAT SECUREVIEW 3.0 PLATFORM.SECUREVIEW VPN SUPPORT - SV CURRENTLY HAS BEEN INTEGRATED WITH CISCO AND ARUBU VPN
CONCENTRATORS. MANY SITES HAVE ESTABLISHED OPERATIONAL ENVIRONMENTS WITH JUNIPER AND
SONICWALL VPN CONCENTRATORS. INTEGRATING SV WITH ADDITIONAL COMMERCIAL VPN CONCENTRATORS
WILL ALLOW ENABLE SITES TO REUSE EXISTING INFRASTRUCTURE, AVOID TRAINING STAFF ON NEW CONCENTRATORS
AND LOWER OVERALL COST TO ACQUIRE SV CAPABILITIES.
2. SECUREVIEW IMPROVED DISPLAY HANDLING - SURFMAN REPLACEMENT Â€“ PROVIDES MULTI-MONITOR
SUPPORT, SUPPORT FOR INTEL, AND AMD GRAPHICS CARDS, BETTER PERFORMANCE, AND BETTER INTEGRATION
WITH MULTIVIEW.
3. SECUREVIEW PLATFORM AUTHENTICATION - PROVIDES THE UIVM WITH USER AUTHENTICATION AND AUDITING.
ALSO PROVIDES THE ABILITY TO HIDE VMS ON A PER-USER BASIS. CAPABILITY HAS BEEN REQUESTED BY
SEVERAL SV SITES.
4. SECUREVIEW SNAPSHOT VM - ALLOW THE SVSM TO INITIATE A SNAPSHOT ON A REMOTE SECUREVIEW
CLIENT MACHINE (SNAPSHOT SAVED ON THE SV CLIENT MACHINE).SECUREVIEW APPLICATION INTEGRATION API - ADD SUPPORT IN MULTIVIEW FOR THIRD PARTY APPLICATION
DEVELOPMENT EXTENDING THE USEFULNESS OF CROSS DOMAIN COMPOSITING TO INDIVIDUAL APPLICATIONS. MONTHLY REPORTS REQUIRED
